{
  "texts": [
    "This is achieved by assigning varying levels of importance to different channels, based on their relevance to the final classification outcome.The channel attention module facilitates the assignment of adaptive weights to different features through the process of squeezing and expanding the feature channels.",
    "This approach results in fewer parameters when compared to the attention model for feature maps, thereby reducing the potential risk of overfitting.",
    "Experimental resultsThe proposed RCA network's performance was assessed through a set of experiments utilizing three public remote sensing scene image datasets: RSSCN7, PatternNet, and EuroSAT.",
    "The experimental configurations, outcomes, and a thorough analysis of the findings are comprehensively presented below.",
    "Dataset description RSSCN7 datasetThe RSSCN7 dataset was publicly released in 2015 by Wuhan University, containing a total of 2800 images across seven distinct scene categories: industry, grass, residential, field, forest, lake, parking lot, and river."
  ]
}